&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;PRIMARY CARE LINK WORKER&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours: 22.5hrs per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working Pattern: Wednesday, Thursday and Friday (7.5hrs per day)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;£12.65 per hour&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Site: &lt;strong&gt;Acomb &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an opening for a Primary Care Link Worker to join our existing team here at York Medical Group. The ideal candidate should be friendly and approachable, have excellent customer services, good IT skills and be a flexible team player. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main duties include&lt;/strong&gt;; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Under the direction of York CVS implement patient referrals from within YMG and provide a personalised package of support to individuals as appropriate. Develop good working relationships with colleagues and GP’s in order to identify patients who would benefit from the promotion of social prescribing. Build and maintain effective partnership with voluntary sector providers and statutory services and highlight gaps in services for development. Working across a significant level of multi-agencies, support patients in a planned and structured way by co-producing personalised care plans to improve health and well-being outcomes. Ability to engage with patients in one to one appointments but also to facilitate group work. Keep accurate patient records and product outcomes and data as required for data collection and reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interested candidates should review the job description and person spec prior to completing the application form. Queries can be directed to Kay Wilson at &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;kaywilson5@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Closing date: 18th November 2020&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;We reserve the right to close the advert earlier should we feel we have sufficient suitable applications. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
